---
title: Marker
desc: Case study for Marker. A construction group in both commercial & residential arena.
---
extends layouts/_layout
block content
	+header('', 'header__burger_dark')
	.product.marker
		.product__head
			.embelish__1
				img(src="img/shapes/l-blue-wiggle-1.svg" alt="")
			.product__center.center
				.product__wrap
					.product__stage.stage(data-aos="animation-scale-y") Design & Development
					h1.product__title.title.h1(data-aos="animation-scale-y" data-aos-delay="150") Marker
					.product__info.h5(data-aos="animation-scale-y" data-aos-delay="300") A construction group in both commercial & residential arena.
		.product__bg(style="background-image: url('img/case-marker-screens.png')")
		.product__body
			.product__center.center
				.product__row
					.product__overview.h4(data-aos="animation-scale-y") Overview
					.product__content.content(data-aos="animation-scale-y" data-aos-delay="200")
						p The company rebranded in 2017 and their website needed to match the rebrand.
						p We were able to resolve the goal by taking a minimal and modern approach to the design. The code base was designed to be clean and optimized, which allowed for the website to load fast, animate well, and stand the test of time. The website includes animations, video backgrounds, fullscreen slider, image lazy loading, and more!
				.product__preview
					.img__container
						img.product__pic.js-parallax(data-scale="1.25" data-delay=".01" data-orientation="up" src="img/case-marker-home.png" alt="")
						
			.desc
				.desc__center.center
					.desc__gifs
						+descGif('img/case-marker-gif.gif', 'Scroll & Hover Effects', 'Effects were added to make sure that the content pages were engaging.')
						.embelish__2
							img(src="img/shapes/l-blue-blob-3.svg" alt="")
							img.js-parallax(data-scale="1.2" data-delay=".5" data-orientation="up" src="img/shapes/l-blue-blob-4.svg" alt="")
					.desc__list
						+descPreview('img/case-marker-1.png', '')
						+descPreview('img/case-marker-2.png', '200')
					+descButtons('/sla', '/bpi')
	+footerTiny